    'Ibu bapa/penjaga boleh mengambil borang permohonan di sekolah yang ingin dimohon.' => 'Parents/guardians can pick up the application form at the school they wish to apply to.',
    'Pihak sekolah/institusi mesti mencetak borang permohonan kemasukan dari laman sesawang Sistem Maklumat Prasekolah Kebangsaan (SMPK).' => 'The school/institution must print the admission application form from the website of the National Preschool Information System (SMPK).',
    'Borang permohonan yang lengkap diisi berserta dokumen-dokumen berkaitan hendaklah dihantar ke sekolah yang dimohon.' => 'Completed application form along with related documents should be sent to the school applied for.',
    'Klik sini untuk ke Sistem Maklumat Prasekolah Kebangsaan.' => 'Click here to go to the National Preschool Information System.',
    'Syarat-syarat kemasukan murid ke kelas prasekolah adalah seperti berikut:' => 'The conditions for student admission to preschool classes are as follows:',
    'Surat Siaran Kementerian Pelajaran Malaysia Bil. 2 Tahun 2012 - Hanya untuk Warganegara Malaysia sahaja dan dipilih menerusi JK Pemilihan.' => 'Malaysian Ministry of Education Bulletin No. 2 Year 2012 - Only for Malaysian Citizens and selected through JK Penitang.',
    'Jawatankuasa Pemilihan murid dianggotai oleh:' => 'The Student Selection Committee consists of:',
    'Guru Besar' => 'Headmaster',
    'Penolong Kanan' => 'Senior Assistant',
    'Guru Prasekolah' => 'Preschool Teacher',
    'Guru Tahap 1 dan 2' => 'Level 1 and 2 teachers',
    'Seorang wakil komuniti' => 'A community representative',
    'Klik sini untuk ke Sistem Maklumat Prasekolah Kebangsaan' => 'Click here to go to the National Preschool Information System',
    'Pendidikan Sekolah Rendah' => 'Primary School Education',
    'Pendaftaran' => 'Registration',
    'PENDAFTARAN' => 'REGISTRATION',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Pendidikan Rendah Wajib' => 'Operating Policy of Compulsory Primary Education',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Pengecualian Daripada Mengikuti Pendidikan Wajib (Penangguhan Ke Tahun 1)' => 'Operating Policy Exemption from Following Compulsory Education (Deferral to Year 1)',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Kemasukan Awal Kanak-Kanak Di Bawah Umur Ke Tahun 1' => 'Operating Policy for Early Admission of Children Under the Age of 1',
    'Permohonan Pengecualian Daripada Mengikuti Pendidikan Wajib Di Peringkat Rendah Dan Menjalankan Persekolahan Di Rumah (Home Schooling)' => 'Application for Exemption from Following Compulsory Education at Primary Level and Conducting Home Schooling',
    'Pendaftaran Murid Tahun 1 kalendar akademik sesi 2024/2025 dibuka pada 1 Mei 2023 hingga 30 Jun 2023 di pautan' => 'Student registration for Year 1 of the 2024/2025 academic calendar session is open from 1 May 2023 to 30 June 2023 at the link',
    'bagi kanak-kanak yang lahir dari 2.1.2017 hingga 1.1.2018.' => 'for children born from 2.1.2017 to 1.1.2018.',
    'Kembali ke Pendidikan Sekolah Rendah' => 'Back to Primary School Education',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Pendidikan Rendah Wajib' => 'Operating Policy of Compulsory Primary Education',
    'Pengenalan' => 'Introduction',
    'Dasar ini bertujuan memastikan setiap ibu bapa warganegara yang menetap di Malaysia yang mempunyai anak mencapai umur enam tahun pada hari pertama tahun persekolahan semasa, mestilah mendaftarkannya di sekolah rendah. Di samping itu juga, ibu bapa perlu memastikan anak yang didaftarkan akan terus menjadi murid di sekolah rendah sepanjang tempoh pendidikan rendah.' => 'This policy aims to ensure that every citizen parent residing in Malaysia who has a child who reaches the age of six on the first day of the current school year, must enroll them in primary school. In addition, parents need to ensure that their registered child will continue to be a student in primary school throughout the period of primary education.',
    'Penyataan Dasar' => 'Statement of Policy',
    'Pendidikan wajib adalah satu undang-undang yang memerlukan setiap ibu bapa warganegara Malaysia yang menetap di Malaysia hendaklah memastikan bahawa jika anaknya mencapai umur enam tahun pada hari pertama bulan Januari dalam tahun persekolahan semasa, anak itu didaftarkan di sekolah rendah. Tempoh pendidikan wajib adalah selama enam tahun, iaitu tempoh pendidikan rendah.' => 'Compulsory education is a law that requires every parent of a Malaysian citizen residing in Malaysia to ensure that if their child reaches the age of six on the first day of January in the current school year, that child is enrolled in primary school. The period of compulsory education is for six years, which is the period of primary education.',
    'Punca Kuasa' => 'Source of Power',
    'Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550) : Subseksyen 29A(1), (2), (3) dan (4).' => 'Education Act 1996 (Act 550) : Subsection 29A(1), (2), (3) and (4).',
    'Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 14/2002: Pelaksanaan Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah 2003 bertarikh 27 November 2002.' => 'Specialized Circular No. 14/2002: Implementation of Compulsory Education at Primary Level 2003 dated 27 November 2002.',
    'Garis Panduan Pelaksanaan Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah tahun 2003.' => 'Guidelines for the Implementation of Compulsory Education at Primary Level in 2003.',
    'Kaedah Pelaksanaan' => 'Methods Of Implementation',
    'Melaksanakan proses pendaftaran yang bermula dengan permohonan dan pengesahan sebelum kanak-kanak mendaftar pada hari pertama persekolahan.' => 'Implement the registration process that begins with the application and verification before the child registers on the first day of school.',
    'Mematuhi kriteria pelaksanaan pendidikan wajib dari segi tempoh pendidikan dan kanak-kanak yang terlibat.' => 'Adhere to the criteria for the implementation of compulsory education in terms of the period of education and the children involved.',
    'Peringatan dari segi implikasi perundangan berikutan kegagalan ibu bapa memastikan anaknya mengikuti pendidikan wajib.' => 'A reminder in terms of legal implications following the failure of parents to ensure that their children attend compulsory education.',
    'Penalti' => 'Penalty',
    'Kegagalan ibu bapa memastikan anaknya mengikut pendidikan wajib merupakan satu kesalahan dari segi undang-undang. Ibu bapa yang disabitkan dengan kesalahan boleh dikenakan denda tidak melebihi lima ribu ringgit atau dipenjarakan tidak lebih enam bulan atau kedua-duanya sekali.' => 'Failure of parents to ensure that their children follow compulsory education is a legal offence. Parents who are convicted of an offense can be fined not more than five thousand ringgit or imprisoned for not more than six months or both.',
    'Tarikh Kuatkuasa :' => 'Effective Date :',
    '1 Januari 2003.' => '1 January 2003.',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Pengecualian Daripada Mengikuti Pendidikan Wajib (Penangguhan Ke Tahun 1)' => 'Operating Policy Exemption from Following Compulsory Education (Deferral to Year 1)',
    'Penangguhan ke Tahun 1 adalah merupakan satu pengecualian daripada mengikuti pendidikan wajib berdasarkan kohort umur yang diberikan kepada kanak-kanak yang memerlukannya. Namun demikian, penangguhan ini hanyalah satu keistimewaan dan bukannya hak. Persekolahan biasa adalah diutamakan kepada kanak-kanak kerana ia merupakan satu cara untuk kanak-kanak berinteraksi di antara satu sama lain.' => 'Deferral to Year 1 is an exemption from attending compulsory education based on the age cohort given to children who need it. However, this deferral is only a privilege and not a right. Regular schooling is preferred for children because it is a way for children to interact with each other.',
    'Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550)' => 'Education Act 1996 (Act 550)',
    'Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 14/2002: Pelaksanaan Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah 2003 bertarikh 27 November 2002.' => 'Specialized Circular Letter No. 14/2002: Implementation of Compulsory Education at Primary Level 2003 dated 27 November 2002.',
    'Garis Panduan Pelaksanaan Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah Tahun 2003.' => 'Guidelines for the Implementation of Compulsory Education at Primary Level in 2003.',
    'Kes permohonan penangguhan kemasukan ke Tahun 1' => 'Case of application for postponement of admission to Year 1',
    'Diputuskan oleh Ketua Pengarah Pelajaran Malaysia (KPPM) selaku Ketua Pendaftar Institusi Pendidikan dan Guru' => 'Decided by the Director General of Education Malaysia (KPPM) as the Chief Registrar of Educational Institutions and Teachers',
    'Kategori permohonan pengecualian ialah:' => 'The categories of exemption applications are:',
    'kes-kes yang tertakluk di bawah Seksyen 29A - merupakan permohonan ibu bapa kohort murid yang lahir pada atau selepas 2 Januari hingga 15 Januari tahun persekolahan semasa;' => 'cases subject to Section 29A - are applications from parents of cohorts of students born on or after January 2 to January 15 of the current school year;',
    'kes-kes yang tidak tertakluk di bawah Seksyen 29A - merupakan permohonan ibu bapa murid yang lahir sebelum 2 Januari tahun persekolahan semasa.' => 'cases that are not subject under Section 29A - are applications from parents of students born before January 2 of the current school year.',
    'Pelaksanaan Pengecualian Pendidikan Wajib' => 'Implementation of Exemption from Compulsory Education',
    'Pemohon hendaklah mengemukakan alasan-alasan yang munasabah berdasarkan prinsip utama pengecualian kepada Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia.' => 'Applicants must present reasonable reasons based on the main principle of exemption to the Ministry of Education Malaysia.',
    'Golongan murid yang diberi pertimbangan khas untuk pengecualian ialah:' => 'The students who are given special consideration for exemption are:',
    'Murid kaum Asli dan Bumiputera Sabah dan Sarawak yang tinggal jauh di pedalaman dan secara tradisinya masih mengamalkan hidup secara berpindah randah;' => 'Pupils of the Asli and Bumiputera tribes of Sabah and Sarawak who live far inland and traditionally still practice a nomadic lifestyle;',
    'Murid istimewa seperti yang ditetapkan, contohnya melalui Peraturan-Peraturan Pendidikan Khas di bawah Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550); dan' => 'Special students as prescribed, for example through the Special Education Regulations under the Education Act 1996 (Act 550); and',
    'Lain-lain golongan yang ditentukan oleh KPPM.' => 'Other groups determined by KPPM.',
    'Permohonan yang boleh dipertimbangkan untuk pengecualian daripada mengikuti pendidikan wajib di peringkat rendah adalah seperti berikut:' => 'Applications that can be considered for exemption from attending compulsory education at primary level are as follows:',
    'Murid yang mencapai umur enam tahun pada 1 Januari tahun persekolahan semasa yang memohon untuk menangguhkan kemasukan ke Tahun 1 ke tahun berikutnya; dan' => 'Pupils who reach the age of six on January 1 of the current school year who apply to postpone entry into Year 1 to the following year; and',
    'Lain-lain permohonan.' => 'Other applications.',
    "Permohonan dikemukakan oleh ibu bapa/penjaga kanak-kanak kepada Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri." => "The application is submitted by the child's parent/guardian to the State Education Department.",
    'Murid mesti mengikuti pendidikan rendah di sekolah sehingga keputusan permohonan penangguhan diluluskan.' => 'Pupils must attend primary education at school until the decision on the deferment application is approved.',
    'Permohonan menggunakan borang permohonan (Borang PPW 2) dan dokumen sokongan yang disahkan :' => 'Application using the application form (Form PPW 2) and certified supporting documents:',
    'Satu (1) salinan kad pengenalan bapa (depan dan belakang);' => "One (1) copy of the father's identity card (front and back);",
    'Satu (1) salinan kad pengenalan ibu (depan dan belakang);' => "One (1) copy of the mother's identity card (front and back);",
    'Satu (1) salinan sijil lahir anak (depan dan belakang);' => "One (1) copy of the child's birth certificate (front and back);",
    'Satu (1) salinan bukti pendaftaran kemasukan ke Tahun 1;' => 'One (1) copy of proof of enrollment to Year 1;',
    'Satu (1) salinan asal laporan doktor; dan' => "One (1) original copy of the doctor's report; and",
    'Dokumen lain jika berkenaan.' => 'Other documents if applicable.',
    '28 Jun 2003' => '28 June 2003',
    'Dasar Pengoperasian Kemasukan Awal Kanak-Kanak Di Bawah Umur Ke Tahun 1' => 'Operating Policy for Early Admission of Children Under the Age of 1',
    'Kemasukan awal kanak-kanak di bawah umur ke Tahun 1 pada setiap tahun persekolahan berdasarkan permohonan daripada ibubapa. Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia (KPM) akan mempertimbangkan permohonan kemasukan awal bagi kanak-kanak bawah umur warganegara Malaysia yang lahir mulai 2 Januari hingga 15 Januari pada tahun persekolahan berkenaan.' => 'Early admission of children under the age of 1 to Year 1 in each school year based on application from parents. The Malaysian Ministry of Education (KPM) will consider early admission applications for Malaysian minors born from January 2 to January 15 in the school year in question.',
    'Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 10/1998 - Kelonggaran Syarat Kemasukan Kanak-Kanak Di Bawah Umur Ke Tahun 1 bertarikh 7 Mei 1998.' => 'Specialized Circular Letter No. 10/1998 - Relaxation of Admission Requirements for Children Under the Age of 1 dated May 7, 1998.',
    'Kanak-kanak telah mengikuti mengikuti pendidikan prasekolah / tadika.' => 'The children have attended pre-school/kindergarten education.',
    'Kanak-kanak mencapai tahap yang munasabah dari segi ‘mental and reading age’.' => "Children reach a reasonable level in terms of 'mental and reading age'.",
    'Kanak-kanak perlu menghadiri sesi modul saringan dan modul temu bual yang dikendalikan oleh pegawai di jabatan pendidikan negeri bagi memastikan kesahihan perkara 1 dan 2.' => 'Children need to attend screening module sessions and interview modules conducted by officials at the state education department to ensure the validity of items 1 and 2.',
    'Pertimbangan permohonan adalah berdasarkan merit ’case by case’ tertakluk kepada kekosongan tempat di sekolah yang dimohon.' => "Application consideration is based on merit 'case by case' subject to the availability of places in the applied school.",
    'Permohonan hendaklah dikemukakan kepada jabatan pendidikan negeri berkenaan dengan menyertakan bersama-sama sijil lahir, surat pengesahan prasekolah / tadika dan laporan kemajuan murid yang telah disahkan.' => 'The application must be submitted to the relevant state education department by including the birth certificate, pre-school/kindergarten confirmation letter and student progress report that has been verified.',
    'Jabatan pendidikan negeri hendaklah memanjangkan semua permohonan dan dokumen sokongan kepada Pengarah Bahagian Pengurusan Sekolah Harian, KPM.' => 'The state education department must forward all applications and supporting documents to the Director of Day School Management Division, KPM.',
    'Semua permohonan kemasukan murid di bawah umur ke Tahun 1 hendaklah diproses oleh Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri terlebih dahulu sebelum dipanjangkan ke KPM untuk pertimbangan.' => 'All applications for the admission of students under the age of 1 must be processed by the State Education Department first before being forwarded to the MoE for consideration.',
    'Keputusan Jawatankuasa Penilaian KPM adalah muktamad.' => 'The decision of the MoE Evaluation Committee is final.',
    '7 Mei 1998' => '7 May 1998',
    'Permohonan Pengecualian Daripada Mengikuti Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah dan Menjalankan Persekolahan di Rumah (Home Schooling)' => 'Application for Exemption From Following Compulsory Education at Primary Level and Conducting Home Schooling',
    'Home Schooling adalah merupakan satu kaedah persekolahan di rumah yang diberikan kepada kanak-kanak yang memerlukannya seperti mempunyai masalah kesihatan kronik dan memerlukan jagaan rapi oleh ibu bapa/ pihak penjaga. Namun demikian, ia hanyalah satu keistimewaan dan bukannya hak. Kanak-kanak diutamakan mengikuti sesi persekolahan seperti biasa kerana proses pengajaran dan pembelajaran yang dilaksanakan di sekolah membolehkan mereka berinteraksi di antara satu sama lain.' => 'Home schooling is a method of home schooling given to children who need it such as having chronic health problems and needing close care by parents/guardians. However, it is only a privilege and not a right. Children are given priority to attend school sessions as usual because the teaching and learning process implemented at school allows them to interact with each other.',
    'Tujuan' => 'Purpose',
    'Memberi peluang kepada kanak-kanak yang mengalami masalah kesihatan yang kronik dan memerlukan penjagaan yang rapi oleh ibu bapa/ penjaga untuk mendapat pendidikan formal di rumah.' => 'Giving opportunities to children who suffer from chronic health problems and need close care by parents/guardians to get formal education at home.',
    'Kaedah Pelaksanaan' => 'Methods of Implementation',
    'Pelaksanaan Dasar' => 'Policy Implementation',
    'Subseksyen 29A (2), Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550) memperuntukkan “Menteri boleh, jika difikirkan wajar dan demi kepentingan murid atau awam untuk berbuat demikian, melalui perintah yang disiarkan dalam Warta, mengecualikan mana-mana murid atau mana-mana golongan murid daripada kehendak supaya mengikuti pendidikan wajib, sama ada secara mutlak atau tertakluk kepada apa-apa syarat yang difikirkannya patut dikenakan, dan boleh pada bila-bila masa menurut budi bicaranya membatalkan pengecualian itu atau membatalkan atau mengubah atau menambah syarat-syarat itu”.' => 'Subsection 29A (2), Education Act 1996 (Act 550) provides that "The Minister may, if deemed appropriate and in the interest of students or the public to do so, by order published in the Gazette, exclude any student or any group of students from the will to attend compulsory education, either absolutely or subject to any conditions it deems appropriate to impose, and may at any time at its discretion cancel the exemption or cancel or change or add to those conditions".',
    'Garis Panduan Pelaksanaan Pendidikan Wajib di Peringkat Rendah Tahun 2003.' => 'Guidelines for the Implementation of Compulsory Education at Primary Level in 2003.',
    'Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 2/2005: Garis Panduan Memproses Permohonan Pengecualian Daripada Mengikuti Pendidikan Wajib Di Peringkat Rendah bertarikh 31 Mei 2005.' => 'Specialized Circular Letter No. 2/2005: Guidelines for Processing Applications for Exemption from Following Compulsory Education at Primary Level dated 31 May 2005.',
    'Permohonan Home Schooling boleh dibuat melalui Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri di seluruh negara menggunakan borang yang telah disediakan.' => 'Applications for Home Schooling can be made through the State Department of Education throughout the country using the form that has been prepared.',
    'Kes permohonan pengecualian daripada mengikuti pendidikan wajib dan menjalankan persekolahan di rumah (Home Schooling) dirujuk kepada Ketua Pengarah Pelajaran Malaysia (KPPM) untuk mendapat ulasan dan kemudiannya diangkat kepada Menteri Pendidikan untuk keputusan.' => 'The case of application for exemption from attending compulsory education and conducting home schooling (Home Schooling) is referred to the Director-General of Education Malaysia (KPPM) for comment and then raised to the Minister of Education for a decision.',
    'Secara amnya, syarat tersebut adalah seperti berikut:' => 'In general, the conditions are as follows:',
    'pemohon hendaklah terdiri daripada warganegara Malaysia;' => 'applicants must be Malaysian citizens;',
    'pemohon mestilah memiliki kelulusan ikhtisas perguruan;' => 'applicants must have a teaching qualification;',
    'salah seorang ibu bapa mestilah berkesanggupan untuk menjadi pengajar kepada kanak-kanak tersebut secara sepenuh masa di rumah;' => 'one of the parents must be able to tutor the child full-time at home;',
    'kurikulum kebangsaan wajib digunakan;' => 'the national curriculum must be used;',
    'berkemampuan untuk menyediakan prasrana pendidikan yang kondusif dan sempurna untuk tujuan pengajaran dan pembelajaran;' => 'able to provide a conducive and perfect educational infrastructure for teaching and learning purposes;',
    'lawatan ke rumah pemohon akan dilakukan oleh pegawai Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia, Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri dan Pejabat Pendidikan Daerah untuk tujuan memastikan kesesuaian prasarana Home Schooling;' => "visits to the applicant's home will be conducted by officials from the Malaysian Ministry of Education, the State Education Department and the District Education Office for the purpose of ensuring the suitability of the Home Schooling infrastructure;",
    'pemohon hendaklah membenarkan Pegawai daripada Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia, Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri atau Pejabat Pendidikan Daerah untuk melawat rumah pada bila-bila masa hari persekolahan bagi tujuan pemantauan proses pengajaran & pembelajaran;.' => 'applicants must allow officials from the Malaysian Ministry of Education, State Education Department or District Education Office to visit the home at any time during the school day for the purpose of monitoring the teaching & learning process;.',
    'kanak-kanak yang diberi kelulusan Home Schooling tidak dibenarkan sama sekali untuk menghadiri sama ada secara tuisyen harian swasta atau kerajaan; dan' => 'children who are approved for Home Schooling are not allowed to attend either private or government daily tuition; and',
    'sekiranya didapati pemohon melanggar syarat-syarat yang terkandung dalam kelulusan yang diberikan oleh pihak Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia, maka kelulusan tersebut adalah dibatalkan. Kanak-kanak tersebut hendaklah didaftarkan semula ke sekolah dengan segera.' => 'if it is found that the applicant violates the conditions contained in the approval given by the Malaysian Ministry of Education, then the approval will be cancelled. The child should be re-registered to school immediately.',
    'Tarikh kuat kuasa pelaksanaan Home Schooling pada 28 Jun 2003.' => 'Effective date of Home Schooling implementation on June 28, 2003.',
    'Pendidikan Sekolah Menengah' => 'Secondary School Education',
    'Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan (Harian)' => 'National High School (Daily)',
    'Pengurusan Asrama Harian' => 'Daily Hostel Management',
    'Program Kesihatan Di Sekolah' => 'School Health Program',
    'Kokurikulum' => 'Co-curriculum',
    'Pendidikan Menengah Rendah adalah untuk murid-murid yang berumur 13 hingga 15 tahun (Tingkatan Satu hingga Tingkatan Tiga) dan diberikan pendedahan pelbagai bidang ilmu dengan menggunakan bahasa kebangsaan sebagai bahasa pengantar utama. Pendidikan Menengah Atas disediakan kepada murid-murid berumur 16 hingga 17 tahun (Tingkatan Empat hingga Tingkatan Lima) menjurus kepada aliran sastera, sains, agama, teknik, vokasional dan kemahiran termasuk menyediakan murid-murid untuk melanjutkan pelajaran ke peringkat pendidikan tinggi atau alam pekerjaan.' => 'Lower Secondary Education is for students aged 13 to 15 years (Level One to Level Three) and is given exposure to various fields of knowledge using the national language as the main language of instruction. Senior Secondary Education is provided to students aged 16 to 17 years (Form Four to Form Five) aimed at the flow of literature, science, religion, technique, vocational and skills including preparing students to continue their education to higher education or employment.',
    'Kembali ke Pendidikan Sekolah Menengah' => 'Back to Secondary School Education',
    'Melalui Penempatan:' => 'Through Placement:',
    'Guru kelas Tahun 6 SK/SRAB/SJKC /SJKT menggunakan aplikasi APDM (Modul e-Daftar Menengah) bagi murid warganegara sahaja berdasarkan Borang Permohonan Penempatan Sekolah (BPPS) yang dilengkapkan oleh ibu bapa/penjaga.' => 'Year 6 SK/SRAB/SJKC/SJKT class teachers use the APDM (Secondary e-Register Module) application for citizen students only based on the School Placement Application Form (BPPS) completed by parents/guardians.',
    'Melalui Permohonan:' => 'Through Application:',
    'Murid Bukan Warganegara boleh memohon menggunakan Borang PU(A)275 Jadual Pertama melalui Unit Perhubungan dan Pendaftaran di JPN. Borang boleh diperolehi dari Pejabat Pendidikan Daerah yang berhampiran.' => 'Non-citizen students can apply using Form PU(A)275 First Schedule through the Liaison and Registration Unit at JPN. Forms can be obtained from the nearest District Education Office.',
    'SENARAI SEKOLAH' => 'LIST OF SCHOOLS',
    'KPM telah menyediakan tempat penginapan yang kondusif dan selamat kepada murid-murid yang kurang berkemampuan serta tinggal jauh daripada sekolah.' => 'KPM has provided a conducive and safe place to stay for students who are less able and live far from school.',
    'Kemudahan asrama yang disediakan adalah bertujuan melahirkan insan (murid) yang cemerlang dalam aspek intelek iaitu kurikulum dan kokurikulum serta seimbang dari segi jasmani dan rohani seperti yang diaspirasikan oleh Falsafah Pendidikan Kebangsaan.' => 'The dormitory facilities provided aim to produce people (students) who excel in the intellectual aspects of the curriculum and co-curriculum as well as balanced in terms of physical and spiritual as aspired by the National Education Philosophy.',
    'Pengurusan asrama harian melaksanakan aktiviti murid berpandukan Buku Panduan Pengurusan Asrama Harian yang berpandukan kepada Surat-Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas yang dikeluarkan oleh KPM.' => 'Daily dormitory management implements student activities guided by the Daily Dormitory Management Guidebook which is guided by the Specialized Circulars issued by the Ministry of Education and Culture.',
    'KPM menubuhkan JK Induk 3K (Kebersihan, Kesihatan dan Keselamatan) yang dipengerusikan oleh Timbalan Menteri Pelajaran bagi menangani isu-isu nasional berkaitan 3 aspek di atas. Bahagian Pengurusan Sekolah Harian dipertanggungjawabkan untuk melaksanakan Program 3K ini.' => 'MoE established JK Induk 3K (Cleanliness, Health and Safety) chaired by the Deputy Minister of Education to deal with national issues related to the above 3 aspects. The Day School Management Division is responsible for implementing this 3K Program.',
    'Kebersihan:' => 'Cleanliness:',
    'Personaliti diri warga sekolah yang cemerlang dan persekitaran sekolah yang bersih, indah dan kondusif dalam membantu proses pengajaran dan pembelajaran yang berkualiti dan berkesan.' => 'The excellent personality of the school members and the clean, beautiful and conducive school environment in helping the quality and effective teaching and learning process.',
    ' Sihat, cergas dan cerdas dari segi jasmani, emosi , rohani dan intelek supaya murid dapat mengawal dan mengurus diri dalam membantu meningkatkan pencapaian akademik dan pembangunan sahsiah diri.' => ' Healthy, fit and intelligent in terms of physical, emotional, spiritual and intellectual so that students can control and manage themselves in helping to improve academic achievement and personal development.',
    'Kesihatan:' => 'Health:',
    'Keselamatan:' => 'Security:',
    ' Suasana yang selamat di dalam atau di luar sekolah boleh meningkatkan keyakinan dan kekuatan dalaman diri (jati diri murid) daripada sebarang pengaruh dan ancaman luar.' => ' A safe atmosphere inside or outside of school can increase confidence and inner strength (student identity) from any external influence and threat.',
    'Taarifan' => 'Inform',
    'Skop dan Bidang Tugas' => 'Scope and Area of ​​Duties',
    '1. Bertanggungjawab merancang Pelan Tindakan Pengurusan Kebersihan iaitu;' => '1. Responsible for planning the Cleanliness Management Action Plan which is;',
    'Menentukan program pembangunan kebersihan murid dilaksanakan di sekolah' => 'Determine the student hygiene development program to be implemented in the school',
    'Menyelaras aktiviti-aktiviti program kebersihan sekolah dengan agensi-agensi berkaitan' => 'Coordinate school hygiene program activities with related agencies',
    'Menentukan keperluan-keperluan kebersihan untuk kesejahteraan murid-murid di sekolah' => 'Determine the hygiene requirements for the well-being of students at school',
    'Merancang keperluan sumber kewangan dan tenaga dalam Pendidikan Kebersihan' => 'Planning financial and energy resource requirements in Hygiene Education',
    'Mengenal pasti keperluan latihan kepada warga sekolah' => 'Identify training needs for school members',
    'Memastikan syarat-syarat perjanjian dan bidang tugas berkaitan dengan perjanjian/kontrak seperti syarikat pembersihan, pengusaha kantin sekolah, pengusaha dewan makan asrama, pembekal makanan RMT dan SBT serta pembekal susu sekolah.' => 'Ensure the terms of the agreement and the scope of work related to the agreement/contract such as cleaning companies, school canteen operators, dormitory dining hall operators, RMT and SBT food suppliers and school milk suppliers.',
    '2. Mewujudkan polisi kebersihan dan kepimpinan yang berkaitan dengan pengurusan kebersihan murid.' => '2. Create hygiene and leadership policies related to student hygiene management.',
    '3. Melaksanakan pemeriksaan, pemantauan dan penilaian kebersihan murid dan sekolah;' => '3. Carry out inspection, monitoring and evaluation of student and school cleanliness;',
    'Mewujud serta melaksanakan manual penjagaan kebersihan murid dan program kebersihan sekolah.' => 'Create and implement a student hygiene care manual and school hygiene program.',
    'Mengkaji dan menilai keberkesanan program secara berterusan' => 'Review and evaluate the effectiveness of the program continuously',
    '4. Menyediakan pelan kontigensi kebersihan untuk menangani kes-kes seperti banjir, jerebu, keracunan makanan dan lain-lain.' => '4. Prepare a hygiene contingency plan to deal with cases such as floods, haze, food poisoning and others.',
    '5. Meningkatkan kerjasama dengan agensi-agensi yang berkaitan program kebersihan' => '5. Improve cooperation with agencies related to hygiene programs',
    '6. Menyediakan laporan secara berkala.' => '6. Prepare reports periodically.',
    'Cadangan Pelaksanaan Aktiviti' => 'Suggested Activity Implementation',
    'Melaksanakan program kebersihan seperti Program Penjagaan Gigi dan Mulut, Program Bebas Kutu, Program Cuci Tangan, Program Penjagaan Kuku, Program Kemas Diri, dan Program Membasmi Kudis Buta.' => 'Implement hygiene programs such as Dental and Mouth Care Program, Flea Free Program, Hand Washing Program, Nail Care Program, Personal Grooming Program, and Blind Scabies Eradication Program.',
    'Melaksanakan pertandingan kebersihan seperti Pertandingan Kebersihan, Pertandingan landskap, Pertandingan Kantin, Pertandingan Angkat Kelas, Pertandingan Melukis dan Mewarna, dan Pertandingan Kuiz, Pidato dan Bahas.' => 'Conducting hygiene competitions such as Cleanliness Competition, Landscaping Competition, Canteen Competition, Class Raising Competition, Drawing and Coloring Competition, and Quiz, Speech and Debate Competition.',
    'Melaksanakan pameran.' => 'Conducting exhibitions.',
    'Melaksanakan program-program lain seperti Program Bebas Denggi dan menyediakan sudut keceriaan serta sekolah kawasan Larangan Merokok.' => 'Implement other programs such as the Dengue Free Program and provide a fun corner and schools in a No Smoking area.',
    'DASAR PERLAKSANAAN KEGIATAN KOKURIKULUM' => 'CO-CURRICULUM ACTIVITY IMPLEMENTATION POLICY',
    'Kegiatan kokurikulum ertinya apa-apa kegiatan yang dirancang daripada proses pengajaran dan pembelajaran di luar bilik darjah (kurikulum) yang memberikan murid peluang untuk menambah, mengukuh dan mengamalkan kemahiran dan nilai-nilai yang dipelajari di bilik darjah.' => 'Co-curricular activity means any activity planned from the teaching and learning process outside the classroom (curriculum) that gives students the opportunity to add, strengthen and practice the skills and values ​​learned in the classroom.',
    'Dalam Warta Kerajaan bertarikh 28 Disember 1967, No. 5652 (Peraturan Kursus Pengajian) Sekolah 1956, kegiatan ini dikenali sebagai "Kegiatan Kumpulan".' => 'In the Government Gazette dated 28 December 1967, No. 5652 (Study Course Regulations) School 1956, this activity is known as "Group Activity".',
    'Dalam Warta Kerajaan bertarikh 31 Disember 1997, Jld. 41, No. 26, Tambahan No. 94, Perundangan A.P.U. (A) 531, Akta Pendidikan 1996, Peraturan-peraturan (Kokurikulum Kebangsaan) telah memberi takrif Kokurikulum iaitu :' => 'In the Government Gazette dated 31 December 1997, Vol. 41, No. 26, Supplement No. 94, A.P.U. Legislation (A) 531, Education Act 1996, Regulations (National Co-Curriculum) have defined Co-Curriculum which is:',
    'Kegiatan kokurikulum di sekolah kerajaan dan bantuan kerajaan akan mengandungi yang berikut:' => 'Co-curricular activities in government and government-aided schools will include the following:',
    'Penyertaan dalam sukan dan permainan.' => 'Participation in sports and games.',
    'Penyertaan dalam persatuan dan kelab.' => 'Participation in associations and clubs.',
    'Penyertaan dalam pasukan pakaian seragam.' => 'Participation in uniformed teams.',
    'Lain-lain kegiatan sebagaimana ditentukan oleh Menteri Pendidikan.' => 'Other activities as determined by the Minister of Education.',
    'DASAR UTAMA (1) KEGIATAN KOKURIKULUM ADALAH SEBAHAGIAN DARIPADA KURIKULUM KEBANGSAAN' => 'MAIN POLICY (1) CO-CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES ARE PART OF THE NATIONAL CURRICULUM',
    'Rujuk Seksyen 18, Akhta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550)' => 'Refer to Section 18, Education Act 1996 (Act 550)',
    'Kurikulum Kebangsaan ialah suatu program pendidikan yang termasuk kurikulum dan kegiatan kokurikulum yang merangkumi semua pengetahuan, kemahiran, norma, nilai, unsur kebudayaan dan kepercayaan untuk membantu perkembangan seseorang murid dengan sepenuhnya dari segi jasmani, rohani, mental dan emosi serta untuk menanam dan mempertingkatkan nilai moral yang diingini dan untuk menyampaikan pengetahuan.' => 'The National Curriculum is an educational program that includes curriculum and co-curricular activities that include all knowledge, skills, norms, values, cultural elements and beliefs to help the development of a student fully in terms of physical, spiritual, mental and emotional as well as to instill and enhance moral values desired and to impart knowledge.',
    'Subperaturan 3(1) Peraturan-Peraturan Pendidikan (Kurikulum Kebangsaan) 1997 yang diterbitkan sebagai PU(A) 531/97.' => 'Subregulation 3(1) of the Education (National Curriculum) Regulations 1997 published as PU(A) 531/97.',
    'Melaksanakan kokurikulum di sekolah adalah WAJIB.' => 'Implementing co-curriculum at school is MANDATORY.',
    'Kegagalan @ Keengganan melaksanakan kegiatan kokurikulum adalah suatu kesalahan yang jika disabitkan bersalah boleh dijatuhi hukuman denda atau penjara atau pun kedua-duanya sekali di bawah penalti am.' => 'Failure @ Refusal to carry out extracurricular activities is an offense that if convicted can be sentenced to a fine or imprisonment or both under the general penalty.',
    'Seksyen 135 Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550 ): Penalti Am.' => 'Section 135 of the Education Act 1996 (Act 550 ): General Penalty.',
    '“(1) Seseorang yang melakukan kesalahan di bawah Akta 550 yang baginya tiada penalti diperuntukkan dengan nyata, boleh, apabila disabitkan, didenda tidak melebihi lima ribu ringgit atau dipenjarakan selama tempoh tidak melebihi enam bulan atau kedua-duanya.”' => '"(1) A person who commits an offense under Act 550 for which no penalty is expressly provided, may, upon conviction, be fined not exceeding five thousand ringgit or imprisoned for a period not exceeding six months or both."',
    '“(2) Seseorang yang melakukan suatu kesalahan di bawah Akta 550 ini boleh, dalam hal suatu kesalahan yang berterusan, apabila disabitkan, dikenakan hukuman denda harian yang tidak melebihi lima ratus ringgit sebagai tambahan kepada apa-apa penalti lain yang boleh dikenakan kepadanya di bawah Akta 550 ini berkenaan dengan kesalahan itu, bagi setiap hari kesalahan itu terus dilakukan.”' => '"(2) A person who commits an offense under Act 550 may, in the case of a continuing offence, upon conviction, be subject to a daily fine not exceeding five hundred ringgit in addition to any other penalty that may be imposed on him under This Act 550 is in relation to that offence, for every day that the offense continues to be committed.”',
    'DASAR UTAMA (2) PENYERTAAN MURID DALAM KEGIATAN KOKURIKULUM ADALAH WAJIB' => 'MAIN POLICY (2) STUDENT PARTICIPATION IN CO-CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES IS MANDATORY',
    'Matlamat gerakerja kokurikulum yang dikehendaki ialah penyertaan setiap orang pelajar. Setiap pelajar hendaklah mengambil bahagian sekurang-kurangnya dalam salah satu gerakerja pakaian seragam, satu kegiatan persatuan atau kelab dan satu kegiatan sukan atau permainan.” – {Perkara 5.1 Surat Pekeliling ikhtisas Bil 1/1985 KP(BS)8591/Jld. II(29)}.' => 'The desired goal of co-curricular activities is the participation of every student. Every student must participate in at least one of the uniform activities, one association or club activity and one sports or game activity." - {Article 5.1 Circular Letter No. 1/1985 KP(BS)8591/Vol. II(29)}.',
    'Sekolah mewujudkan peluang yang seluas-luasnya kepada murid menyertai kegiatan kokurikulum yang mereka minati. – {Untuk tujuan ini Pengetua/Guru Besar telah diperuntukkan kuasa untuk menubuhkan kelab/persatuan di sekolah seperti dalam Peraturan 4 Peraturan-Peraturan Pendidikan (Persatuan Sekolah) 1998 yang diterbitkan sebagai PU(A)196/98.}.' => 'The school creates the widest possible opportunity for students to participate in extracurricular activities that they are interested in. – {For this purpose the Principal/Headmaster has been allocated the authority to establish clubs/associations in schools as per Regulation 4 of the Education (School Association) Regulations 1998 published as PU(A)196/98.}.',
    'Penyertaan, kehadiran dan pencapaian murid dalam kegiatan kokurikulum hendaklah direkod dan diberi penilaian. – {Hal ini ditegaskan dalam Perkara 8.2.1 Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil 1/1985 dan Perkara 2.1 Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil 2/1986}' => 'Student participation, attendance and achievement in co-curricular activities must be recorded and evaluated. – {This is confirmed in Article 8.2.1 of the Specialized Circular Letter No. 1/1985 and Article 2.1 of the Specialized Circular Letter No. 2/1986}',
    'Ketidakhadiran murid dalam kegiatan kokurikulum yang murid itu telah mendaftarkan diri untuk menyertainya adalah suatu kesalahan yang menyebabkan murid tersebut boleh dikenakan tindakan disiplin jika disabitkan bersalah seperti tindakan ke atas kesalahan ponteng sekolah atau ponteng kelas. – {Hal ini hendaklah dimaktubkan dalam Buku Undang-Undang dan Peraturan Sekolah dan perlu diketahui oleh murid-murid dan ibu bapa mereka}.' => 'The absence of a student in an extra-curricular activity that the student has registered to participate in is an offense that causes the student to be subject to disciplinary action if convicted, such as truancy or truancy. – {This should be enshrined in the Law Book and School Regulations and should be known by the students and their parents}.',
    'DASAR UTAMA (3) PENYERTAAN SEMUA GURU ADALAH WAJIB' => 'MAIN POLICY (3) PARTICIPATION OF ALL TEACHERS IS MANDATORY',
    'Penyertaan semua guru sebagai penjawat atau pengkhidmat awam dalam mengurus, menyelia dan mengelola kegiatan kokurikulum di sekolah adalah wajib.' => 'The participation of all teachers as civil servants or civil servants in managing, supervising and organizing co-curricular activities in schools is mandatory.',
    'Penyertaan semua guru adalah dikehendaki bagi mempastikan keberkesanan pelaksanaan gerakerja kokurikulum di sekolah” (Perkara 5.2 dalam Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 1/1985.).' => 'The participation of all teachers is required to ensure the effectiveness of the implementation of co-curricular activities in schools" (Article 5.2 in the Expert Circular No. 1/1985.).',
    'Setiap orang guru di sekolah hendaklah, secara bertulis, diberi tugas dan tanggung jawab yang spesifik, terperinci, dan kuantitatif dalam bidang kokurikulum di sekolah, seperti yang dilakukan dalam bidang kurikulum.' => 'Each teacher in the school must, in writing, be given specific, detailed, and quantitative duties and responsibilities in the field of co-curriculum in the school, as is done in the field of curriculum.',
    'Keengganan guru melaksanakan tugas dan tanggung jawab yang telah diperuntukan adalah suatu kesalahan daripada segi keperluan perkhidmatan atau kepatuhan dan kebertanggungjawaban penjawat awam atau pun moral dan wibawa keguruan yang boleh dikenakan tindakan disiplin mengikut “Perintah-perintah Am Pegawai Awam (Kelakuan dan tatatertib)(Bab D)”.' => "The teacher's refusal to carry out the tasks and responsibilities that have been allocated is an offense in terms of service requirements or compliance and accountability of civil servants or even the morals and authority of teachers that can be subject to disciplinary action according to the \"General Orders of Civil Servants (Conduct and Discipline)\" (Chapter D).",
    'DASAR UTAMA (4) PERLAKSANAAN “KEGIATAN KOKURIKULUM”' => 'MAIN POLICY (4) IMPLEMENTATION OF "CO-CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES"',
    '“Kegiatan kokurikulum” yang dilaksanakan di sekolah hendaklah merupakan apa-apa kegiatan yang dirancang lanjutan daripada proses pengajaran dan pembelajaran (P&P) dalam bilik darjah yang memberikan murid-murid peluang untuk menambah, mengukuh dan mengamalkan pengetahuan, kemahiran dan nilai-nilai yang dipelajari di dalam bilik darjah.” {Peraturan 2 dalam Peraturan-Peraturan Pendidikan (Kurikulum Kebangsaan) 1997}.' => '"Co-curriculum activities" carried out in schools should be any activities planned as an extension of the teaching and learning process (P&P) in the classroom that give students the opportunity to add, strengthen and practice the knowledge, skills and values ​​learned in in the classroom." {Regulation 2 in the Education (National Curriculum) Regulations 1997}.',
    'Setiap kegiatan kokurikulum yang dilaksanakan hendaklah dirancang dengan maksud mempunyai matlamat, objektif, kaedah pelaksanaan dan kurikulum kegiatan serta skema penilaian yang pragmatis dan progresif.' => 'Every co-curricular activity implemented should be planned with the aim of having goals, objectives, implementation methods and activity curriculum as well as a pragmatic and progressive evaluation scheme.',
    'Setiap kegiatan kokurikulum yang dilaksanakan hendaklah mengandungi elemen-elemen pengetahuan, pengalaman dan kemahiran baru serta nilai-nilai murni yang membantu membangunkan intelek, jasmani, emosi dan rohani murid secara seimbang.' => "Every co-curricular activity carried out must contain elements of new knowledge, experience and skills as well as noble values ​​that help develop students' intellect, body, emotions and spirituality in a balanced way.",
    'DASAR UTAMA (5) PENYERTAAN “BERAMAI-RAMAI”' => 'PRINCIPAL POLICY (5) PARTICIPATION "CROWDED"',
    'Pelaksanaan kegiatan kokurikulum di sekolah hendaklah berasaskan prinsip penyertaan beramai-ramai tanpa ada unsur-unsur diskriminasi atau paksaan tetapi menfokus kepada peningkatan perpaduan dan integrasi di kalangan murid-murid. (Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 17/2000 bertarikh 16 November 2000).' => 'The implementation of co-curricular activities in schools should be based on the principle of mass participation without any elements of discrimination or coercion but focusing on increasing unity and integration among students. (Expert Circular Letter No. 17/2000 dated November 16, 2000).',
    'Kegiatan kokurikulum yang dilaksanakan di sekolah hendaklah bersifat merentas disiplin, bersepadu dan tidak bersifat eksklusif. Penyertaan adalah terbuka kepada semua pelajar.' => 'Co-curricular activities carried out in schools should be cross-disciplinary, integrated and not exclusive. Participation is open to all students.',
    'DASAR SOKONGAN DALAM PERLAKSANAAN KOKURIKULUM DI SEKOLAH' => 'SUPPORT POLICY IN THE IMPLEMENTATION OF CO-CURRICULUM IN SCHOOL',
    'Sekolah-sekolah khususnya yang kurang kemudahan untuk gerakerja kokurikulum ini hendaklah menggalakkan pelajar-pelajarnya mengambil bahagian dalam membuat kerja-kerja amal untuk masyarakat setempat; bergotong royong memperbaiki kawasan sekolah; gerakerja-gerakerja yang menekankan perpaduan kaum, ketatanegaraan, moral dan sebagainya yang sesuai bagi pendidikan menyeluruh dan pembentukan keperibadian. – {Perkara 5.3 Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 1/1985, KP(BS)8591/Jld.(929)}.' => 'Schools in particular that lack facilities for extracurricular activities should encourage their students to participate in doing charity work for the local community; work together to improve the school grounds; activities that emphasize racial unity, polity, morality and so on that are suitable for comprehensive education and personality formation. – {Article 5.3 of Circular No. 1/1985, KP(BS)8591/Vol.(929)}.',
    'Kegiatan kokurikulum di sekolah boleh dilaksanakan dengan penglibatan dan penyertaan anggota masyarakat setempat. – {Rujuk Subperkara 4.2.1 dan Subperkara 5.2 dalam Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 4/1985 KP. 8591-11(32) bertajuk “Sekolah Sebagai Institusi Masyarakat”}.' => 'Extracurricular activities at school can be implemented with the involvement and participation of local community members. – {Refer to Sub-item 4.2.1 and Sub-item 5.2 in the Special Circular No. 4/1985 KP. 8591-11(32) entitled "School as a Community Institution"}.',
    'Kementerian Pendidikan amat menggalakkan murid-murid bergiat dalam kegiatan Pasukan Pakaian Seragam yang terdapat di sekolah-sekolah. Selaras dengan dasar tersebut, guru-guru dan murid-murid juga dibenarkan menyertai aktiviti seperti perkhemahan, perbarisan dan kursus yang dianjurkan dari semasa ke semasa oleh agensi-agensi kerajaan atau oleh pertubuhan bukan kerajaan yang berdaftar. -  (Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 24/1998).' => 'The Ministry of Education strongly encourages students to be active in the activities of the Uniform Team found in schools. In accordance with the policy, teachers and students are also allowed to participate in activities such as camps, parades and courses organized from time to time by government agencies or by registered non-government organisations. - (Special Circular No. 24/1998).',
    'Kementerian Pendidikan membenarkan pihak sekolah menganjurkan program lawatan pendidikan murid semasa waktu persekolahan secara terancang. Kementerian juga menggalakkan penglibatan ibu bapa yang berminat untuk menyertai lawatan-lawatan tersebut. -  (Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 12/2000).' => 'The Ministry of Education allows schools to organize student educational visits during school hours in a planned manner. The Ministry also encourages the involvement of parents who are interested in participating in the visits. - (Expert Circular No. 12/2000).',
    'Sesuai dengan matlamat Falsafah Pendidikan Negara, Kementerian Pendidikan ingin menegaskan bahawa murid-murid di sekolah perlu diberi ruang untuk mengembangkan potensi mereka secara menyeluruh dan bersepadu agar mereka menjadi insan yang seimbang dari segi intelek, rohani, emosi dan jasmani. - (Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 18/2000).' => 'In line with the goals of the National Education Philosophy, the Ministry of Education would like to emphasize that students at school need to be given the space to develop their potential comprehensively and integrated so that they become intellectually, spiritually, emotionally and physically balanced people. - (Special Circular No. 18/2000).',
    'Sekolah hendaklah memberi penghargaan kepada guru-guru dan pelajar-pelajar atau orang perseorangan (atas penyertaan, penglibatan dan pencapaian masing-masing dalam bidang kokurikulum di sekolah). Penghargaan tidak hanya terbatas kepada kejayaan / kemenangan semata-mata, tetapi hendaklah juga diberi kepada pelajar-pelajar yang mempunyai sifat disiplin yang baik. - (Subperkara 8.2.4 Surat Pekeliling Ikhtisas Bil. 1/1985).' => 'The school must give appreciation to teachers and students or individuals (for their participation, involvement and achievements in the extracurricular field at school). Appreciation is not only limited to success / victory, but should also be given to students who have good discipline. - (Sub-item 8.2.4 of Specialized Circular Letter No. 1/1985).',
    'Sekolah mewujudkan peluang kepada murid-murid mengembangkan bakat dan potensi diri masing-masing dalam bidang-bidang kokurikulum yang mereka minati ke peringkat yang lebih tinggi sehinggalah ke peringkat antarabangsa.' => 'The school creates opportunities for students to develop their individual talents and potential in the areas of the curriculum they are interested in to a higher level and even to an international level.',
    'Murid-murid juga sebaik-baiknya diberi peluang memperagakan bakat dan kecemerlangan masing-masing kepada masyarakat awam' => 'The students should also be given the opportunity to demonstrate their talents and excellence to the public',
    'Pendidikan Lepas Menengah' => 'Pre University',
    'Tingkatan 6' => 'Form 6',
    'Matlamat' => 'Goals',
    'Piagam Pelanggan Kemasukan Murid Ke Tingkatan 6' => 'Customer Charter for Student Admission to Form 6',
    'Kerangka Konseptual' => 'Conceptual Framework',
    'Syarat Kemasukan' => 'Entry requirements',
    'Penjenamaan Semula' => 'Rebranding',
    'Tempoh Pengajian' => 'Duration of study',
    'Pusat Tingkatan 6' => 'Form 6 Center',
    'Kurikulum' => 'Curriculum',
    'Pentaksiran & Yuran' => 'Assessments & Fees',
    'Akta Pendidikan 1996 (Akta 550), menyatakan “pendidikan lepas menengah” ertinya Pendidikan yang disediakan untuk seseorang yang sudah tamat mengikut Pendidikan lepas menengah, tetapi tidak termasuk Pendidikan Tinggi.' => 'The Education Act 1996 (Act 550), states that "post-secondary education" means Education provided to a person who has completed post-secondary Education, but does not include Higher Education.',
    'Tingkatan 6 telah mula beroperasi di sekolah menengah kerajaan dan sekolah menengah bantuan kerajaan lebih daripada 50 tahun dahulu. Pada masa itu, bilangan kelas Tingkatan 6 yang di tawarkan ialah minimum 2 kelas dan maksimum 22 kelas. Terdapat 2 bidang yang ditawarkan iaitu bidang Sains Sosial (Kemanusiaan dan Agama) dan Bidang Sains.' => 'Form 6 has started operating in government secondary schools and government aided secondary schools more than 50 years ago. At that time, the number of Form 6 classes offered was a minimum of 2 classes and a maximum of 22 classes. There are 2 fields offered which are Social Sciences (Humanities and Religion) and Science.',
    'Mulai tahun 2008, Langkah penambahbaikan dari segi pengurusan dan fungsi Tingkatan 6 serta kebajikan murid diberi tumpuan untuk mendaikan proses pengajaran dan pembelajaran Tingkatan 6 lebih menarik serta menyediakan suasana pembelajaran yang kondusif. Cadangan penambahbaikan yang disarankan oleh Kementerian Pendidikan Malaysia pada tahun 2008 merangkumi beberapa aspek seperti pengurusan dan pentadbiran, pelaksanaan pengajaran dan pembelajaran, penyelidikan an penulisan ilmiah, kemudahan fizikal, serta peranan Jabatan Pendidikan Negeri dan Pejabat Pendidikan Daerah.' => 'Starting in 2008, improvement steps in terms of management and function of Form 6 as well as student welfare were focused on making the teaching and learning process of Form 6 more interesting and providing a conducive learning atmosphere. Suggestions for improvement suggested by the Malaysian Ministry of Education in 2008 include several aspects such as management and administration, implementation of teaching and learning, scientific research and writing, physical facilities, as well as the role of the State Education Department and the District Education Office.',
    'Manakala pelaksanaan sistem pentaksiran baharu STPM telah dimulakan pada tahun 2012 setelah diluluskan oleh Mesyuarat Jemaah Menteri (MJM) pada 4 Januari 2012.' => "While the implementation of STPM's new assessment system was started in 2012 after being approved by the Cabinet Meeting (MJM) on 4 January 2012.",
    'Tempoh pengajian di Tingkatan 6 adalah selama tiga semester. Murid yang telah menamatkan pengajian menengah atas dan telah menduduki peperiksaan Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM), layak untuk ditawarkan pengajian di Tingkatan 6 jika memenuhi syarat umum dan syarat khusus bagi bidang yang ditawarkan.' => 'The study period in Form 6 is for three semesters. Pupils who have completed upper secondary education and have sat for the Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM) examination, are eligible to be offered studies in Form 6 if they meet the general requirements and specific requirements for the field offered.',
    'Kembali ke Pendidikan Lepas Menengah' => 'Return to Pre University Education',
    'Meningkatkan taraf pendidikan ke arah yang lebih tinggi.' => 'Improve the level of education towards a higher level.',
    'Memberi pendidikan berdasarkan sistem penggal dan berdaya saing yang tinggi.' => 'Provide education based on term system and highly competitive.',
    'Memberi pendidikan yang setara dengan program prauniversiti yang lain.' => 'Provides education equivalent to other pre-university programs.',
    'Memastikan murid lulusan Sijil Tinggi Persekolahan Malaysia (STPM) mempunyai nilai kebolehpasaran yang tinggi.' => 'Ensure that students who graduate from the Malaysian Higher School Certificate (STPM) have a high marketability value.',
    'Membentuk kepemimpinan menuju ke arah membina Negara Bangsa meliputi aspek perpaduan, patriotisme, dan jati diri bagi mendokong aspirasi nasional.' => 'Forming leadership towards building a Nation includes aspects of unity, patriotism, and identity to support national aspirations.',
    'Tingkatan 6 merupakan laluan pendidikan bagi murid lepasan Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM) untuk mengembangkan bakat dan kreativiti seterusnya menjadi generasi muda berimpak tinggi, glokal dan universal. Mereka ini akhirnya membawa kesejahteraan kepada negara disamping mendapat kelayakan yang memenuhi standard antarabangsa.' => 'Form 6 is an educational pathway for Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM) graduates to develop talent and creativity to become a high-impact, glocal and universal young generation. These people finally bring prosperity to the country in addition to getting qualifications that meet international standards.',
    'Lepasan Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM) ke Tingkatan 6 menerima tawaran dalam tempoh 19 hari bekerja sebelum tarikh murid mendaftar.' => "Graduates of Sijil Pelajaran Malaysia (SPM) to Form 6 receive offers within 19 working days before the student's registration date.",
    'Kerangka Konseptual Tingkatan 6 yang merangkumi dua komponen utama iaitu kurikulum dan kokurikulum.' => 'Form 6 Conceptual Framework which includes two main components namely curriculum and co-curriculum.',
    'Matlamat pendidikan Tingkatan 6 adalah bagi membentuk kepimpinan menuju ke arah Membina Negara Bangsa meliputi aspek perpaduan, patriotisme, jati diri bagi mendokong aspirasi nasional. Mendidik murid secara menyeluruh berdasarkan Falsafah Pendidikan Kebangsaan dan berupaya memikul tanggungjawab, prihatin, berinovatif, matang, berjiwa kendiri, berpandangan jauh, keteguhan jati diri dan berbudaya penyayang.' => 'The goal of Form 6 education is to form leadership towards building a Nation, covering aspects of unity, patriotism, identity to support national aspirations. Educate students comprehensively based on the National Education Philosophy and are able to shoulder responsibility, be considerate, innovative, mature, independent, far-sighted, strong in identity and have a caring culture.',
    'Tiga kemahiran utama yang diterapkan dalam pendidikan Tingkatan 6 ialah kemahiran kognitif, kemahiran manipulatif dan kemahiran insaniah (soft skills).' => 'The three main skills applied in Form 6 education are cognitive skills, manipulative skills and soft skills.',
    'Tempoh pengajian di Tingkatan 6 adalah selama 1½ tahun yang merangkumi tiga penggal. Penggal 1 bermula dari bulan Mei hingga November, Penggal 2 bermula dari bulan Januari hingga Mei dan Penggal 3 bermula dari bulan Mei hingga November.' => 'The study period in Form 6 is for 1½ years which includes three terms. Term 1 starts from May to November, Term 2 starts from January to May and Term 3 starts from May to November.',
    'Sijil Tinggi Persekolahan Malaysia (STPM) mendapat pengiktirafan daripada Kerajaan Malaysia, Jabatan Perkhidmatan Awam (JPA), dan Cambridge Assessment, England. Sijil STPM turut diterima oleh JPA untuk menjawat perjawatan dalam perkhidmatan kerajaan. Murid yang memperoleh keputusan cemerlang dalam peperiksaan STPM dan kokurikulum layak memohon untuk melanjutkan pelajaran ke Institusi Pengajian Tinggi (IPT) dalam dan luar negara.' => 'The Malaysian Higher Education Certificate (STPM) is recognized by the Malaysian Government, the Public Service Department (JPA), and Cambridge Assessment, England. The STPM certificate is also accepted by JPA for employment in the government service. Pupils who obtain excellent results in the STPM and co-curricular examinations are eligible to apply to further their studies at Institutions of Higher Education (HEIs) within and outside the country.',
    'Kegiatan kokurikulum Tingkatan 6 mesti dinilai berdasarkan format atau kaedah yang tetap dan diiktiraf agar keesahan dan kebolehpercayaan hasil penilaian itu tidak dipertikaikan, lebih-lebih lagi apabila markah kokurikulum dijadikan sebahagian daripada markah penilaian kemasukan ke Institusi Pengajian Tinggi Awam (IPTA). Penstrukturan dan penjenamaan semula Tingkatan 6 turut melibatkan perubahan pengoperasian kokurikulum. Oleh itu, pengurusannya boleh diadakan secara berasingan daripada kegiatan kokurikulum arus perdana.' => 'Form 6 co-curricular activities must be evaluated based on a fixed and recognized format or method so that the validity and reliability of the evaluation results are not disputed, especially when the co-curricular score is made part of the admission evaluation score to Public Institutions of Higher Education (IPTA). The restructuring and rebranding of Form 6 also involves changes in the operation of the co-curriculum. Therefore, its management can be held separately from mainstream co-curricular activities.',
    'Syarat Kemasukan ke Tingkatan 6' => 'Admission Requirements to Form 6',
